comments: Sengun (HOU) moves alongside Duren's (DET) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.

Stewart (DET) commits a foul on Smith Jr. (HOU) immediately after he secures the rebound. The contact was not deemed a transition take foul because the transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Sengun (HOU) establishes himself in Ivey's (DET) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Green (HOU) is moving alongside Ivey's (DET) path and Ivey loses the ball by his own merit as they come together during the drive.
Knox II (DET) moves toward Bullock Jr.'s (HOU) path and marginal contact occurs as Bullock Jr. turns to defend the drive.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Duren (DET) mishandles the pass, and is the last to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
VanVleet (HOU) attempts to go for the steal and initiates contact with Burks' (DET) arm, causing Burks to lose control of the ball.
Burks (DET) briefly places an arm around Sengun (HOU) as he moves over the screen and the contact is marginal.
Sengun (HOU) firms up over his left foot in Burks' (DET) path and as the pick is set.
Duren (DET) legally contests VanVleet's (HOU) jump shot attempt.

In pursuit of the rebound, Green (HOU) brings his arm toward the ball and marginal contact occurs with Knox II's (DET) arm. The marginal contact does not affect Knox II's ability to secure the rebound.
Smith Jr. (HOU) contests Ivey's (DET) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
VanVleet (HOU) releases his right arm as he and Duren (DET) mutually engage in pursuit of the rebound and marginal contact occurs with Duren's back as he jumps to retrieve the rebound.
